# CS50-s-Introduction-to-Databases-with-SQL---HU
Self-learning repository documenting my journey through Harvard University’s CS50’s Introduction to Databases with SQL. Covers SQL fundamentals, database design, querying, joins, aggregations, normalization, and hands-on problem solving through practical exercises and projects.
## Introduction
This repository contains my notes, exercises, assignments, and practice projects completed while learning SQL and database concepts through Harvard University's CS50 course.

## Topics Covered

- SQL Fundamentals
- Database Design
- SELECT Queries
- Filtering & Sorting
- JOINs
- Aggregations
- Subqueries
- Views & Indexes
- Data Modeling
- Analytical Problem Solving

## Goal
The goal of this repository is to strengthen my SQL, analytical thinking, and database management skills for Data Analyst and Business Analyst roles.
